SIMPLE: inhumane
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: inhumane
<hw>in`hu*mane"</hw> <pr>(⟦icr⟧n`h⟦umac⟧*m⟦amac⟧n")</pr>,
<pos>adj.</pos> <def>not humane; lacking and reflecting lack of pity,
kindness, or compassion; <as>as, humans are innately <ex>inhumane</ex>;
this explains much of the misery and suffering in the world; biological
weapons are considered too <ex>inhumane</ex> to be used</as>.</def>
[Narrower terms: <stype>barbarous, brutal, cruel, fell, roughshod,
savage, vicious</stype>; <stype>beastly, bestial, brute(prenominal),
brutish, cannibalic </stype>; <stype>brutal, cruel</stype>; <stype>cold,
cold-blooded, inhuman, insensate </stype>; <stype>pitiless, unfeeling,
unkind </stype>; <stype>painful (vs. painless) </stype>] <see>Also See:
<er>uncivilized</er>.</see> Antonym: <ant>humane</ant>.⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>inhumanely</ent>⟦br⟧
